### Vulnerability
`_blacklisted[account]` is not initialized. If there is an attack that is able to access this function and change the blacklisting the attacker could change the blacklisting so the user can no longer call the function. The attacker could set the blacklisting as true so the user cannot call the function. The attacker could do this on a new transaction or change the value of the boolean blacklisted on an existing transaction.

### How to take advantage of the vulnerability
The attacker would need to be able to change the blacklisting. The attacker could use a transaction like:

```
approve(IERC20 token, uint256 amount)
unBlacklist(address account)
```

### Description of the vulnerability
An attacker would be able to take advantage of the vulnerability in the following situation:
* Attackers can modify the value of blacklisted[account] to true or false to allow or block the rescue function.
* Attackers can modify blacklisted[account] to true or false on a new transaction or on an existing transaction.
* The attacker will be able to take advantage of the vulnerability if there is an attack that is able to access the function with the ability to modify the boolean blacklisted[account].

